&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 MSK Physiotherapist &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;London&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary £34,170 - £44,880&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Dependent on Experience)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are an MSK Physiotherapist currently working at band 6 and you are seeking a role where you will be assessing and treating a varied caseload of patients and delivering MSK clinics within the community, you might be exactly who we&#39;re looking for!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Healthshare is one of the leading Healthcare providers in the UK. We provide NHS Physiotherapy, Orthopaedic, Rheumatology, MSK Podiatry and Pain Management Services across 19 CCG’s nationwide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have excellent communisation skills as well as an in-depth understanding of MSK Physiotherapy. They must have a flexible, adaptable and innovative approach to work and be able to proactively deliver results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The right candidate will be a HCPC and CSP registered Physiotherapist with a BSc in Physiotherapy and at least 2 years’ experience working in an MSK setting. You will be expected to maintain your own electronic patient records (SystmOne), actively participate in clinical teaching and in-service training sessions, deliver a high standard of patient-centred clinical care, possess a friendly and approachable attitude and apply outstanding team-working, communication and organisational skills to your daily practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Like the sound of this job? Don&#39;t miss out - apply now!&lt;/p&gt;
